<TEXT>
<P>
I'm one of the many viewers delighted with ABC's "Life Goes On." I enjoy it for 
many reasons, one of which is its optimistic portrayal of Down's syndrome, but 
also for another reason. 
</P>
<P>
I wonder how many of the show's fans realize that Patti LuPone, whose Libby 
Thacher is one of the most entertaining TV mothers around, is also one of 
Broadway's best? As Reno Sweeney in the Broadway revival of "Anything Goes," 
Fantine in "Les Miserables" on London's West End and the star of "Evita," she 
is one of today's most versatile and successful stars. 
</P>
<P>
I am pleased that "Life Goes On" allows such a wonderful arena for LuPone to 
display her many talents. Long may it go on! 
</P>
<P>
Daisy Bennett, Rowland Heights 
</P>
