<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHARED TABLES MAY BE THE WAY TO GO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re "Hate to Eat Alone? Try Shared Tables" (Aug. 27): They have been doing it 
for years -- in Austria, Germany and England. 
</P>
<P>
My wife and I once shared a table with a couple in a hotel dining room in 
London. Imagine our surprise and delight when in the course of conversation it 
turned out that my relatives were their best friends. 
</P>
<P>
On lonely business trips abroad, I always looked for a table to share. 
</P>
<P>
HENRY BRUNELL 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth 
</P>
</TEXT>
