<HEADLINE>
<P>
THEY SAY GETTING THERE IS EASY, LEAVING IS THE HARD PART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hulse 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How to get there: Telluride is 65 miles from Montrose, 127 miles from Grand 
Junction, 327 miles southwest of Denver, at an elevation of 8,745 feet. 
</P>
<P>
Beginning Dec. 15, Delta Airlines/SkyWest will inaugurate nonstop flights on 
Saturdays and Wednesdays from LAX. Call (800) 453-9417. 
</P>
<P>
Other service daily from Denver by United Express, (800) 821-7126, and 
Continental Express, (800) 525-0280. 
</P>
<P>
Where to stay: The San Sophia, 330 W. Pacific St., Telluride, Colo. 81435, 
(800) 537-4781. Rates: $70 to $210. 
</P>
<P>
Manitou Hotel, 568 W. Pacific St., Telluride 81435, (800) 233-9292. $50-$150. 
</P>
