</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LISBON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Portugal will hold a presidential election Jan. 13, a spokesman for President 
Mario Soares has announced. 
</P>
<P>
Soares, elected in 1986, is widely expected to run again but has yet to 
announce his candidacy. His term expires in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
