<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FIRE BURNS 100 ACRES OF BRUSH IN AGUA DULCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire burned 100 acres of brush in Agua Dulce on Saturday afternoon before 
firefighters extinguished the blaze, the Los Angeles County Fire Department 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The fire burned in the 32000 block of Agua Dulce Canyon Road, north of the 
Antelope Valley Freeway, said Los Angeles County fire dispatcher Teresa Rios. 
It broke out at about 2:30 p.m. and was controlled in less than two hours, said 
Fire Department spokesman Kerry Brisson. 
</P>
<P>
No structures were threatened and no one was injured, Brisson said. The cause 
of the fire was under investigation. 
</P>
