<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOULD A HANDGUN BAN REALLY HAVE AVERTED DANA POINT DEATH? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The most recent tragedy of the handgun shooting of an 18-year-old boy by a 
16-year-old points up the urgency of the passage of the Brady Bill (H.R. 467), 
which would require a seven-day cooling off period for handgun sales. 
</P>
<P>
At present, this bill is seven votes short of passage in the House of 
Representatives and needs voters to prompt its support by their congressmen 
who, like ours, are still undecided. 
</P>
<P>
The price for delay will be more innocent children killed in the crossfire. 
</P>
<P>
GLENDA ROSEN 
</P>
<P>
Dana Point 
</P>
</TEXT>
