THE WEEK AHEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AIR: The Environmental Protection Agency will hold a public workshop Tuesday to 
discuss its plan for attacking air pollution in the Los Angeles Basin. Federal 
officials will be available at the Baldwin Park Hilton from 2 p.m. to 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
TOXICS PLANT: The State Department of Health Services on Tuesday will discuss a 
proposal by Chem-Clear Inc. to build a hazardous waste treatment plant in 
Vernon. 
</P>
<P>
Residents in nearby Huntington Park oppose the plant, which would be built less 
than a block away from homes and a school. The hearing is at 7 p.m. at 
Huntington Park High School Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
AFFORDABLE HOUSING: In Cerritos, where homes sell in the $300,000-plus range, 
the Planning Commission chairman on Thursday will present the City Council with 
a plan for starting affordable housing programs. 
