in charge of 8,400 armed men and women off-handedly recommends the execution of 
misdemeanor drug users after writing a letter in support of parole for an 
admitted and convicted felon. Where is the consistency in this? He cites 
Milken's willingness to go into dangerous neighborhoods to work. Perhaps Gates 
would recommend parole for our local gang bangers to go into some of those same 
neighborhoods. After all, they would be more than willing and they have already 
killed hundreds of casual drug users. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN C. WILLIS 
