<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENING: LOS ANGELES CONDOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tile entries, fireplaces, private balconies and views of the Hollywood Hills 
are some of the amenities at Manhattan Villas, a 19-unit condominium and 
townhouse development that opens this weekend in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The units have two or three bedrooms, two to 2 1/2 baths and 1,000 to 1,500 
square feet of living space. 
</P>
<P>
Prices range from $152,900 to $224,900, with move-ins expected to begin Oct. 1. 
</P>
<P>
Common areas include a courtyard, lobby and subterranean, gated garage. Monthly 
homeowners dues are about $121 a month. 
</P>
<P>
The project was developed by Lewis Mishreki &amp; Associates. It's open from 11 
a.m. to 6 p.m. Friday through Tuesday at 102 S. Manhattan Place. 
</P>
<P>
Tarzana Townhomes 
</P>
<P>
The 14-unit Cape project by Rigney Development Group opens this weekend at 
18854 Hatteras St. in Tarzana. 
</P>
<P>
The townhouses are designed in a Cape Cod style with three floor plans that 
have three bedrooms, 2 1/2 baths and a bonus area. Shared amenities include 
pool and spa. 
</P>
<P>
Units vary in size from 2,539 to 2,662 square feet and prices range from 
$355,950 to $359,950, with a homeowner's monthly fee of $165.33. The project is 
open today, noon to 5 p.m., and during the same hours on Monday, Friday and on 
weekends. 
</P>
</TEXT>
