<HEADLINE>
<P>
AIRLINE PASSENGERS URGED TO WRITE TROOPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWARK, N.J. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Continental Airlines passengers who travel through Newark International Airport 
will be offered free stationery and postage to write troops in the Middle East. 
</P>
<P>
"We're hoping a lot of people will take time between their coffee and boarding 
to jot a little note," Continental spokeswoman Andrea Pass said. 
</P>
<P>
The airline says 35,000 passengers travel through the Newark airport each day 
on its planes. 
</P>
