<HEADLINE>
<P>
GORBACHEV'S TERMS FOR GULF INITIATIVE LISTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev is willing to discuss Iraq's grievances 
with Kuwait if Baghdad's troops withdraw from the emirate, Italian Foreign 
Minister Gianni De Michelis said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
De Michelis told a news conference after talks with Gorbachev that the Soviet 
leader is prepared to launch an initiative to resolve the crisis, but this 
would hinge on an Iraqi withdrawal and the restoration of Kuwait's sovereignty. 
</P>
<P>
"In this context, he believes that if Iraq agrees to this then it would be 
possible at a diplomatic level to discuss the issues raised by Iraq prior to 
the invasion," he said. 
</P>
