</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tournament most valuable player Kevin Eggert scored six goals to lead 
Capistrano Valley to a 13-7 victory over Miraleste in the championship match of 
the Millikan Tournament at Belmont Palza pool. 
</P>
<P>
Eggert scored seven goals in a 14-7 semifinal victory over Dos Pueblos. He 
scored 27 goals in the five tournament matches for Capistrano Valley (6-0). 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley's Dan Hancock, who scored four goals in each of the semifinal 
and final games and had 21 in tournament, was also named to the all-tournament 
team as was goalie Nick Kittredge and Stod Buckley. 
</P>
