<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UCI WOMEN WIN IN CROSS-COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three UC Irvine runners finished among the first 10 to lead the Anteaters to 
the women's championship of the Fresno State Cross-Country Invitational 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Buffy Rabbitt finished first, winning the 5,000-meter race at Woodward Park in 
17 minutes 2.8 seconds. Irvine's Rayna Cervantes (17:51.3) was sixth and Traci 
Goodrich (17:57.0) seventh, and the Anteaters point total of 75 easily 
outdistanced runner-up Weber State's 95. 
</P>
<P>
Ben Ayers finished third for the Irvine men's team (76 points), which finished 
second to Fresno State (60). Ayers ran 25:17.1 on the five-mile course, 
finishing behind Aaron Mascorro, an Irvine redshirt who ran unattached 
(25:00.6), and Steve Frisone of Cal State Fullerton (25:14.8). 
</P>
<P>
In the Azusa Pacific cross-country invitational, Southern California College's 
Sherri Hall won the 5,000-meter race in 18 minutes 47.2 seconds. Southern 
California College didn't field a full team for the invitational, which was won 
by Azusa Pacific. 
</P>
<P>
In the UC Irvine water polo tournament, USC and UCLA each won their matches and 
will meet for the championship today at 1:40 p.m. at Corona del Mar High 
School. UCLA, the only undefeated team in pool play, defeated Stanford, 12-6, 
and Cal State Long Beach, 8-5. The Bruins were led by Stefan Pollmann, who 
scored five goals against Stanford and four against Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The Trojans, who went 3-1 in pool play, were led by Jason Klingsberg, who 
scored six goals on the day. USC beat UC Irvine, 7-6, and Cal State Los 
Angeles, 14-9. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine, led by Pablo Yrizar who scored two goals in each Anteater loss 
Saturday, also lost to UC Santa Barbara, 11-10. 
</P>
<P>
In the Christ College Irvine men's soccer tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Biola 3, Christ College Irvine 2 -- Biola scored twice in the second half to 
rally and defeat Christ College Irvine in the championship game. Christ College 
Irvine (1-5) took a 2-0 lead in the first half on a pair of goals by Aaron 
Clasen in the first 20 minutes of play. Clasen scored five goals in the two-day 
tournament. Biola (4-2-1) tied the score on Mike Humphries' goal seven minutes 
into the second half, and went ahead when John Buehler scored with four minutes 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
In Anteater invitational women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Northern Iowa 3, UC Irvine 2 -- Northern Iowa won the Anteater Invitational at 
Crawford Hall with a 7-15, 15-8, 15-6, 10-15, 15-4 victory over UC Irvine. 
UCI's Kim Collins had 19 kills in the championship match and teammate Caron 
Pardee added 13. 
</P>
<P>
Northern Iowa's Denise Cuttell was named the tournament's most valuable player. 
Collins and Pardee were named to the all-tournament team. 
</P>
<P>
In a nonconference women's volleyball match: 
</P>
<P>
San Francisco 3, Cal State Fullerton 0 -- Jennifer Cokubun had 14 kills as 
visiting USF (4-5) won, 15-9, 15-6, 15-6. Becky Howlett had 10 kills and 
Stephanie Scofield had 12 digs for the Titans (3-7) 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 0, Seattle Pacific 0 (OT) -- Goalkeeper Jay Nettekoven had 
five saves for the Titans (1-2-2) at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Claremont 4, Southern California College 0 -- Armando Luna, Amir Navab, Sean 
McQuown and Steve Barbarich each scored for host Claremont (1-2-2). Claremont 
goalie Sean Black had four saves. Angel Ruiz had six saves for Southern 
California College (1-5). 
</P>
