<HEADLINE>
<P>
CURRENTS: A GUIDE TO THE BEST OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA; 
</P>
<P>
FOOD; 
</P>
<P>
COOKING BY THE BOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LINDA ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"I BRING THE COOKBOOK page to life by re-creating the look and taste of recipes 
as their authors intended," says professional chef Ruth Hedges. Hedges, well 
aware of the great number of us who read cookbooks like novels -- for pure 
pleasure, with absolutely no intention of actually preparing a recipe -- has 
created Cookbook Fantasies. 
</P>
<P>
"This service is unique, because unlike when dealing with caterers, you can 
control the entire menu," Hedges says. "You get to serve a fantasy meal to 
friends without any effort." So the next time you're planning a party -- 
whether an intimate gathering or a large affair -- -- why not plan on pasta by 
Wolfgang Puck, or blackened snapper by Paul Prudhomme, and a Martha Stewart 
tart for dessert. 
</P>
<P>
 Ruth Hedges Culinary Productions, Cookbook Fantasies; (818) 897-2128. LINDA 
ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Ruth Hedges. Claudia Kunin 
